ACS to Build $371 Million Gas Plant in Brazil, Economista Reports

-- B y   B e n   S i l l s
-- 
2011-08-19T06:01:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-19/acs-to-build-371-million-gas-plant-in-brazil-economista-says.html
Actividades de Construccion y
Servicios SA won a contract to build a 500-megawatt combined-
cycle gas-fired power plant for  MPX Energia SA (MPXE3)  for about 260
million euros ($371 million), El Economista reported.  The plant will be located in the state of Maranhao in the
interior of the country about 1,000 miles from the capital
Brasilia, the newspaper said, without saying how it obtained the
information.  The company aims to have the plant in operation by the end
fo 2013, the newspaper added.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Sills at 
